==English==
===Noun Phrase===
'''rheumatoid arthritis'''

# {{pathology}} A chronic and progressive disease in which the [[immune system]] attacks the [[joint]]s. It is characterised by pain, inflammation and swelling of the joints, stiffness, weakness, loss of mobility and deformity. Tissues throughout the body can be affected, including the skin, [[blood vessel]]s, [[heart]], [[lung]]s, and [[muscle]]s.

====Synonyms====
* [[atrophic arthritis]]

